          <p>
            <strong>Account Information.</strong> You register a phone number or email address when you create a CapCheck account. This information is used to provide our Services to you. You may optionally add other information to your account, such as a profile name and profile picture.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Content Submitted for Analysis.</strong> When you submit content for fact-checking (text, images, audio, or video), this content is processed by our AI systems to provide analysis results. We retain submitted content only as long as necessary to provide the service and improve our systems, unless you request deletion.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>User Support.</strong> If you contact CapCheck User Support, any personal data you may share with us is kept only for the purposes of researching the issue and contacting you about your case.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Managing Your Information.</strong> You can manage your personal information in CapCheck's application Settings. You may request deletion of your account and associated data at any time.
          </p>

          <h3>How We Use Information</h3>
          <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Provide, maintain, and improve our fact-checking Services</li>
            <li>Process and analyze content you submit for verification</li>
            <li>Communicate with you about your account and our Services</li>
            <li>Develop and train our AI systems to improve accuracy</li>
            <li>Detect, prevent, and address fraud, abuse, or technical issues</li>
          </ul>
