            <strong>Anonymized Data for Insights and Reporting.</strong> We may use anonymized, aggregated data derived from user submissions to create and publish trend reports, insights, news content (such as "Trending on CapCheck"), and other informational products. This data is stripped of all personally identifiable information and cannot be traced back to individual users. For example, we might report that "claims about Topic X increased 50% this week" without ever identifying who submitted those claims. We do not operate as a social network and do not publicly associate any content with individual users.
          </p>

